        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 25 at 8:18PM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 818 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Queen City, or near Atlanta, moving northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Domino, Pleasant Hill, Bloomburg, Atlanta, Queen City, Wake Village,
Fouke, Nash, Red Lick, and Texarkana.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 900 PM CDT for
southwestern Arkansas.</instruction>
